----Qt3.2.3 Installation

Basiclly, all we need to do it extract the package Qt3.2.3,

and export two env variables



1. QMAKESPEC  ------to spicify the compiler 
There are three options in windows

Visual C++ 6     : win32-msvc

Visual C++ 7/7.1 : win32-msvc.net

Borland C++      : win32-borland

2. QTDIR--------Qt directory 

Say, we extract it into D:\Qt, then QTDIR shall be D:\Qt



Now let's try to compile a helloworld

The compiler in use is visual c++ 7.1,

In DOS, run the following command:

set QMAKESPEC=win32-msvc   （using vc++6）

set QTDIR=E:\Qt\3.2.3          

Then put the following hello.cpp in D:\projects\qt\hello\

#include <qapplication.h>

#include <qlabel.h>

int main(int argc, char *argv[])

{

   QApplication app(argc, argv);

   QLabel *label = new QLabel("Hello Qt!", 0);

   app.setMainWidget(label);

   label->show();

   return app.exec();

}

"My computer->Properity->Advnced->env variables" to add vc6 and ;E:\Qt\3.2.3\bin into $PATH



D:\projects\qt\hello>qmake -project

hello.pro is obtained

D:\projects\qt\hello>qmake hello.pro

to generate Makefile

D:\projects\qt\hello>nmake

Thus we will get a hello.exe finally.
 







